# {{ .ProjectName }}

A web application built with [Gastro](https://github.com/andrioid/gastro).

## Getting Started

This project pins the gastro CLI in `go.mod` via a `tool` directive, so you
can run it without a global install:

```sh
go tool gastro dev
```

If you prefer a global `gastro` binary on your `PATH`, install it via
[mise](https://mise.jdx.dev/) (`mise use github:andrioid/gastro@latest`) or
`go install github.com/andrioid/gastro/cmd/gastro@latest`, then run:

```sh
gastro dev
```

Then open [http://localhost:4242](http://localhost:4242) in your browser.

## Project Structure

```
pages/          Page templates (.gastro files)
components/     Reusable components (.gastro files)
static/         Static assets (CSS, images, etc.)
main.go         Application entry point
```

## Commands

Any of these can be invoked as `go tool gastro <cmd>` (uses the version
pinned in `go.mod`) or as `gastro <cmd>` (uses whatever is on `PATH`).

| Command             | Description                              |
|---------------------|------------------------------------------|
| `gastro dev`        | Start dev server with hot reload         |
| `gastro build`      | Build a production binary                |
| `gastro generate`   | Regenerate the .gastro/ directory        |
| `go generate ./...` | Same as `gastro generate` (uses the `//go:generate` directive in `main.go`) |

`gastro dev` is the right command for this project because it was scaffolded
by `gastro new`. If you later restructure into a library-mode layout (gastro
embedded in a multi-binary Go module that owns its own `main.go`), switch to
`gastro watch --run '...'`. See [Getting Started — Library Mode](https://github.com/andrioid/gastro/blob/main/docs/getting-started-library.md).

